The problem with this code is that it's trying to add a number and a string
string together, which Tundra doesn't support directly. It needs to convert
convert these two values into numbers before addition. The parseNumber func
function does the job but here we have "11" in quotes so it has to be given
given as an argument of type String not Number.

Here is the corrected code:

```Tundra
def chooseCurrent(groups)  {
  return groups[0].items[0];
}

val groups = [
  {
    name: "archive",
    items: [
      { total: "11" }
     ]
   },
  {
    name: "current",
    items: [
       { total: "27" }
     ]
   }
];

val item = chooseCurrent(groups);
val total = parseNumber(item.total) + 2;

print(total);
```
